Reasoning: 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is a likely category as the paper deals with the operational semantics of a calculus. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is also a likely category as the paper studies an extension of the lambda calculus. 
- cs.TL (Temporal Logic) is a possible category as the paper deals with the evaluation of terms to distributions of values. 
- cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) is a possible category as the paper defines small-step and big-step semantics inductively and coinductively. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is a possible category as the paper studies the expressive power of the obtained system with respect to computable probability distributions.
